{
  "stem": "11771.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Zvi Michaeli.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name was-- Isaac Zvi-- Isaac [INAUDIBLE] Michalowski.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Michalowski or Micaeli.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Born in Ejszyszki.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In that time it was Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "May 15, 1925.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mine age right now is 71.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I left-- I left to come back to the house, [BACKROUND NOISE] since I remember Ejszyszki.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's about 55 years ago, or 70 years ago, whichever you say.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So [INAUDIBLE] now start to be-- in order to portrayed Ejszyszki, at it was, I have to entirely ignore the place where I am interview, ignore America, ignore wherever I was, and come back to Ejszyski.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then I need to be-- to turn over myself to a kid and to describe you the Ejszyszki like it was-- like hundreds and thousands of shtetl in Lithuania and on an Eastern Poland.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Was Ejszyszki also, which a common shtetl, Jewish shtetl, with a yeshiva, with a [NON-ENGLISH] shul with all kind of Jewish activities, like [NON-ENGLISH], with a [NON-ENGLISH], and three shuls, and all kind of activities, Jewish activities, with organizations, like Betar, and Hashomer Hatzair, and Mizrahi, and a nice, beautiful, Jewish youth-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the life was going on normally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were six children-- and, of course, a big family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Besides our family, mom-- my mother's two sisters, my father has a brother with a family, with five children; mine uncle from the mother's side with three children; and the other aunt with two children.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the life was going on so normal, everybody do his duty.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was, that time, a young man going in the yeshiva, learning mainly Jewish studies, Jewish history, mainly about religious things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father was a teacher-- Hebrew and Yiddish, and also in Talmud.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in this kind atmosphere, I grew up.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
